@Tomishiyo It&#39;s a topology-issue.
A cube(&#39;s surface) is also a sphere, topology-wise. It has the same genus. It&#39;s finite. It doesn&#39;t aribitarily cut off.
(Planes have the same genus but aren&#39;t finite. The interior of a sphere - the ball - aribitarily cuts off at, well, the surface. Tori don&#39;t cut off and are finite but they have a higher genus. E.g. spheres have no holes, tori one.)
